{
  "model": "core.chatmessage",
  "pk": 2,
  "fields": {
    "conversation": null,
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "Considering your daily targets and allergies/exclusions, here's a recommendation:\n\nFor a pre-workout snack, aim for something that provides a balance of carbohydrates and protein.\n\nA suitable option could be 1 medium banana (~100 calories, ~25g carbs) paired with 2 tablespoons of almond-free nut butter (e.g., sunflower seed butter) or a non-dairy yogurt alternative (~8g protein). This combo should provide about 120-140 calories, 30-35g carbs, and 8g protein.\n\nIf you prefer something more substantial, consider a small serving of oatmeal with fruit and nuts. However, be sure to check the ingredient list for any peanut or almond contamination.\n\nRemember to stay hydrated by drinking water at least 15-20 minutes before your workout.\n\nHow does this sound? Do you have any other preferences or dietary restrictions I should take into account?",
    "created_at": "2026-03-10T09:21:18.192Z"
  }
},
