  "fields": {
    "conversation": 3,
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "To break the weight plateau, I recommend a combination of increased caloric intake and targeted macronutrient adjustments.\n\n1. **Caloric increase**: Aim for an average daily intake of approximately 2800-2900 kcal to provide your body with the necessary energy to make progress.\n2. **Protein boost**: Increase protein intake to 170-180g (target: P146g) to support muscle growth and maintenance, while also helping with satiety. Consider adding protein-rich foods like:\n\t* Lean beef (100g = 26g protein)\n\t* Fish (salmon, tilapia) (100g = 20-25g protein)\n\t* Greek yogurt (200g = 20g protein)\n3. **Carbohydrate adjustment**: Focus on complex carbohydrates sources and increase intake to 270-280g (target: C261g). Include:\n\t* Brown rice (150g = 30g carbs)\n\t* Quinoa (100g = 20g carbs)\n\t* Sweet potatoes (150g = 25g carbs)\n4. **Healthy fats**: Maintain a consistent intake of healthy fats, aiming for around 60-70g (target: F58g). Include:\n\t* Nuts and seeds (almonds, chia seeds) in moderation\n\t* Avocado (100g = 14g fat)\n\nSample adjustments to your diet:\n\n* Replace Cereals, CREAM OF RICE with brown rice or quinoa.\n* Add lean beef or fish as a protein source.\n\nMonitor your progress and adjust these recommendations as needed. Remember to stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water throughout the day!",
    "created_at": "2026-03-31T08:20:59.405Z"
  }
},
